[N]CANCELLATION NOTICE
CHUNCHULA PIPELINE COMPANY, LLC
[C]LOCAL PIPELINE TARIFF
Containing
RATES, RULES AND REGULATIONS
Applying On
LIQUID HYDROCARBON PRODUCTS
Transported by Pipeline
From and To Points Named Herein
[N]Issued under the authority of 18 CFR ?341.5 - Cancellation of tariff. This tariff is hereby cancelled. The services set forth in this tariff are no longer available in interstate commerce.
Issued on twenty-five (25) days' notice under the authority of 18 C.F.R. ? 341.14. This tariff publication is conditionally accepted subject to refund pending a thirty (30) day review period.
[C]This tariff contains rates that are revised under authority of 18 CFR ?342.3.
The rates in this tariff are expressed in cents per U.S. Gallon and are subject to change as provided by law, also for the transportation of Liquid Hydrocarbon Products, by pipeline to the rules and regulations published herein, revisions hereof.
The provisions published herein will, if effective, not result in an effect on the quality of the human environment.
ISSUED: AUGUST 6, 2015 EFFECTIVE: SEPTEMBER 1, 2015
ISSUED AND COMPILED BY: Steve Miao 1100 Louisiana, Houston, Texas 77002-5227 713-381-4778
[C]GENERAL APPLICATION
The Carrier will receive Liquid Hydrocarbon Products for interstate transportation from the origin points named herein to destination points named herein, subject to the following rules and regulations:
GENERAL RULES AND REGULATIONS
ITEM 5 DEFINITIONS OF TERMS USED IN THIS TARIFF
"Barrel" - Forty-two (42) United States gallons at sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60?F) and equilibrium vapor pressure.
"Carrier" - Means and refers to Chunchula Pipeline Company, LLC.
"Gallon" - Means a U.S. liquid gallon of 231 cubic inches at sixty degrees (60?) Fahrenheit and equilibrium pressure.
"Liquid Hydrocarbon Products" - Means all Specification Products, including mixtures thereof.
"Specification Product" - Means any one of the following products: (a) Propane is a hydrocarbon product conforming to Gas Processors Association (GPA specification HD-5 provided in its latest publication. There shall be no free water content. (b) Butane is a commercial butane conforming to GPA specification as provided in the latest GPA publications. (c) Isobutane is a hydrocarbon product containing not less than ninety-five (95) liquid volume percent isobutane and meeting the volatile sulphur corrosive compounds and dryness specifications specified by the GPA for commercial butane in its latest publication. (d) Normal Butane is a hydrocarbon product containing not less than ninety-five (95) liquid volume percent normal butane and meeting the volatile sulphur corrosive compounds and dryness specifications specified by the GPA for commercial butane in its latest publications. (e) Natural Gasoline is a hydrocarbon product conforming to GPA specifications; however, the natural gasoline shall not contain more than two (2) percent butane by liquid volume.
ITEM 10 MINIMUM TENDER - Shipments will be accepted for transportation under this tariff in quantities of not less than five thousand (5,000) Barrels.
ITEM 15 DESTINATION FACILITIES REQUIRED - Shipments will be received for transportation only when the shipper or consignee has provided the necessary facilities required to receive such shipments as they arrive at destination.
ITEM 20 MEASURING, TESTING AND VOLUME CORRECTIONS - Liquid Hydrocarbon Products tendered to Carrier for transportation may be tested by Carrier prior to receipt from shipper. Quantities shall be measured through meters at point of origin. The volume accepted for transportation will be corrected as to temperature from observed degrees Fahrenheit to sixty degrees (60?) Fahrenheit and further corrected for pressure in accordance with A.P.I. Standard 2534 - Measurement of Liquid Hydrocarbons by Turbine Meter Systems. Transportation charges will be assessed on such corrected volume.
ITEM 25 QUANTITIES DELIVERABLE - Carrier will account to shippers for all quantities received from shippers at origin, less a tender allowance reduction of three-tenths of one percent (0.3%) and will deliver to shippers at destination the quantities received as reduced by such tender reduction allowance.
ITEM 30 PAYMENT OF TRANSPORTATION AND OTHER CHARGES - The shipper or consignee shall pay the transportation and all other lawful charges accruing on Liquid Hydrocarbon Products which have been transported and, if required, shall pay the same before delivery. Transportation charges will be collected on the basis of the net quantities delivered into the pipeline. Liquid Hydrocarbon Products accepted for transportation shall be subject to a first lien for all such charges.
ITEM 35 LIENS AND UNPAID CHARGES - When any Liquid Hydrocarbon Product tendered for transportation hereunder is involved in litigation, or the ownership of which may be in dispute or which may be encumbered by lien or charge of any kind, Carrier may require of shippers an indemnity bond to protect it against all loss.
ITEM 40 LIABILITY OF CARRIER - While in the possession of the property herein described, Carrier shall not be liable for any loss or damage or delay caused by the act of God, public enemy, quarantine, authority of law, strikes, riots, fire, floods, or act of default of shipper or owner, or for any other cause not due to the negligence of Carrier whether similar or dissimilar to the causes herein enumerated. ITEM 45 NOTICE OF CLAIMS - Notice of claims for loss or damage must be made in writing to Carrier within nine (9) months after delivery of the product, or in the case of failure to make delivery, then within nine (9) months after a reasonable time for delivery has elapsed. Suit against Carrier shall be instituted only within two (2) years and one (1) day from the day when notice in writing is given by Carrier to the claimant that Carrier has disallowed the claim or any part or parts thereof specified in the notice. Where the claims are not filed or suits are not instituted thereon in accordance with the foregoing provisions, such claims will not be paid and the Carrier shall not be liable.
ITEM 50 APPORTIONMENT WHEN CURRENT OFFERINGS ARE IN EXCESS OF FACILITIES - When pursuant to tenders hereunder, there shall be offered to Carrier more Liquid Hydrocarbon Products than can be immediately transported, the transportation shall be apportioned among all shippers in proportion to the rate at which deliveries are currently available for shipment under tenders then in effect.
